items.snippet:
Oct 3, 2017 ... Recognizable to most New Yorkers as “that graffiti-covered building on the corner 
of Spring,” 190 Bowery has maintained a mysterious facade since the 
photographer Jay Maisel bought it in 1966 for $102,000 and converted the former 
Germania Bank into a six-story, 72-room home and studio for himself, ...
